{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I have a question for you:"},{"time":3000,"text":"Are you religious?"},{"time":5000,"text":"Please raise your hand right now"},{"time":7000,"text":"if you think of yourself as a religious person."},{"time":10000,"text":"Let's see, I'd say about three or four percent."},{"time":13000,"text":"I had no idea there were so many believers at a TED Conference."},{"time":16000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":18000,"text":"Okay, here's another question:"},{"time":20000,"text":"Do you think of yourself as spiritual"},{"time":22000,"text":"in any way, shape or form? Raise your hand."},{"time":24000,"text":"Okay, that's the majority."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"My Talk today"},{"time":29000,"text":"is about the main reason, or one of the main reasons,"},{"time":31000,"text":"why most people consider themselves"},{"time":33000,"text":"to be spiritual in some way, shape or form."},{"time":35000,"text":"My Talk today is about self-transcendence."},{"time":38000,"text":"It's just a basic fact about being human"},{"time":41000,"text":"that sometimes the self seems to just melt away."},{"time":44000,"text":"And when that happens,"},{"time":46000,"text":"the feeling is ecstatic"},{"time":49000,"text":"and we reach for metaphors of up and down"},{"time":51000,"text":"to explain these feelings."},{"time":53000,"text":"We talk about being uplifted"},{"time":55000,"text":"or elevated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57000,"text":"Now it's really hard to think about anything abstract like this"},{"time":60000,"text":"without a good concrete metaphor."},{"time":62000,"text":"So here's the metaphor I'm offering today."},{"time":65000,"text":"Think about the mind as being like a house with many rooms,"},{"time":68000,"text":"most of which we're very familiar with."},{"time":71000,"text":"But sometimes it's as though a doorway appears"},{"time":74000,"text":"from out of nowhere"},{"time":76000,"text":"and it opens onto a staircase."},{"time":79000,"text":"We climb the staircase"},{"time":81000,"text":"and experience a state of altered consciousness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"In 1902,"},{"time":87000,"text":"the great American psychologist William James"},{"time":89000,"text":"wrote about the many varieties of religious experience."},{"time":92000,"text":"He collected all kinds of case studies."},{"time":94000,"text":"He quoted the words of all kinds of people"},{"time":96000,"text":"who'd had a variety of these experiences."},{"time":98000,"text":"One of the most exciting to me"},{"time":100000,"text":"is this young man, Stephen Bradley,"},{"time":102000,"text":"had an encounter, he thought, with Jesus in 1820."},{"time":105000,"text":"And here's what Bradley said about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":114000,"text":"(Video) Stephen Bradley: I thought I saw the savior in human shape"},{"time":117000,"text":"for about one second in the room,"},{"time":119000,"text":"with arms extended,"},{"time":121000,"text":"appearing to say to me, \"Come.\""},{"time":124000,"text":"The next day I rejoiced with trembling."},{"time":127000,"text":"My happiness was so great that I said I wanted to die."},{"time":130000,"text":"This world had no place in my affections."},{"time":133000,"text":"Previous to this time,"},{"time":135000,"text":"I was very selfish and self-righteous."},{"time":137000,"text":"But now I desired the welfare of all mankind"},{"time":140000,"text":"and could, with a feeling heart,"},{"time":142000,"text":"forgive my worst enemies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"JH: So note"},{"time":148000,"text":"how Bradley's petty, moralistic self"},{"time":150000,"text":"just dies on the way up the staircase."},{"time":152000,"text":"And on this higher level"},{"time":154000,"text":"he becomes loving and forgiving."},{"time":158000,"text":"The world's many religions have found so many ways"},{"time":160000,"text":"to help people climb the staircase."},{"time":162000,"text":"Some shut down the self using meditation."},{"time":164000,"text":"Others use psychedelic drugs."},{"time":166000,"text":"This is from a 16th century Aztec scroll"},{"time":170000,"text":"showing a man about to eat a psilocybin mushroom"},{"time":173000,"text":"and at the same moment get yanked up the staircase by a god."},{"time":177000,"text":"Others use dancing, spinning and circling"},{"time":179000,"text":"to promote self-transcendence."},{"time":181000,"text":"But you don't need a religion to get you through the staircase."},{"time":184000,"text":"Lots of people find self-transcendence in nature."},{"time":187000,"text":"Others overcome their self at raves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190000,"text":"But here's the weirdest place of all:"},{"time":193000,"text":"war."},{"time":195000,"text":"So many books about war say the same thing,"},{"time":197000,"text":"that nothing brings people together"},{"time":199000,"text":"like war."},{"time":201000,"text":"And that bringing them together opens up the possibility"},{"time":204000,"text":"of extraordinary self-transcendent experiences."},{"time":207000,"text":"I'm going to play for you an excerpt"},{"time":209000,"text":"from this book by Glenn Gray."},{"time":211000,"text":"Gray was a soldier in the American army in World War II."},{"time":214000,"text":"And after the war he interviewed a lot of other soldiers"},{"time":217000,"text":"and wrote about the experience of men in battle."},{"time":219000,"text":"Here's a key passage"},{"time":221000,"text":"where he basically describes the staircase."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226000,"text":"(Video) Glenn Gray: Many veterans will admit"},{"time":228000,"text":"that the experience of communal effort in battle"},{"time":231000,"text":"has been the high point of their lives."},{"time":234000,"text":"\"I\" passes insensibly into a \"we,\""},{"time":237000,"text":"\"my\" becomes \"our\""},{"time":239000,"text":"and individual faith"},{"time":241000,"text":"loses its central importance."},{"time":244000,"text":"I believe that it is nothing less"},{"time":246000,"text":"than the assurance of immortality"},{"time":249000,"text":"that makes self-sacrifice at these moments"},{"time":252000,"text":"so relatively easy."},{"time":255000,"text":"I may fall, but I do not die,"},{"time":258000,"text":"for that which is real in me goes forward"},{"time":261000,"text":"and lives on in the comrades"},{"time":263000,"text":"for whom I gave up my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267000,"text":"JH: So what all of these cases have in common"},{"time":270000,"text":"is that the self seems to thin out, or melt away,"},{"time":273000,"text":"and it feels good, it feels really good,"},{"time":275000,"text":"in a way totally unlike anything we feel in our normal lives."},{"time":278000,"text":"It feels somehow uplifting."},{"time":281000,"text":"This idea that we move up was central in the writing"},{"time":284000,"text":"of the great French sociologist Emile Durkheim."},{"time":287000,"text":"Durkheim even called us Homo duplex,"},{"time":289000,"text":"or two-level man."},{"time":291000,"text":"The lower level he called the level of the profane."},{"time":294000,"text":"Now profane is the opposite of sacred."},{"time":297000,"text":"It just means ordinary or common."},{"time":299000,"text":"And in our ordinary lives we exist as individuals."},{"time":302000,"text":"We want to satisfy our individual desires."},{"time":305000,"text":"We pursue our individual goals."},{"time":307000,"text":"But sometimes something happens"},{"time":309000,"text":"that triggers a phase change."},{"time":311000,"text":"Individuals unite"},{"time":313000,"text":"into a team, a movement or a nation,"},{"time":316000,"text":"which is far more than the sum of its parts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319000,"text":"Durkheim called this level the level of the sacred"},{"time":322000,"text":"because he believed that the function of religion"},{"time":324000,"text":"was to unite people into a group,"},{"time":326000,"text":"into a moral community."},{"time":329000,"text":"Durkheim believed that anything that unites us"},{"time":332000,"text":"takes on an air of sacredness."},{"time":334000,"text":"And once people circle around"},{"time":336000,"text":"some sacred object or value,"},{"time":338000,"text":"they'll then work as a team and fight to defend it."},{"time":341000,"text":"Durkheim wrote"},{"time":343000,"text":"about a set of intense collective emotions"},{"time":345000,"text":"that accomplish this miracle of E pluribus unum,"},{"time":348000,"text":"of making a group out of individuals."},{"time":350000,"text":"Think of the collective joy in Britain"},{"time":353000,"text":"on the day World War II ended."},{"time":356000,"text":"Think of the collective anger in Tahrir Square,"},{"time":359000,"text":"which brought down a dictator."},{"time":362000,"text":"And think of the collective grief"},{"time":364000,"text":"in the United States"},{"time":366000,"text":"that we all felt, that brought us all together,"},{"time":369000,"text":"after 9/11."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372000,"text":"So let me summarize where we are."},{"time":375000,"text":"I'm saying that the capacity for self-transcendence"},{"time":377000,"text":"is just a basic part of being human."},{"time":380000,"text":"I'm offering the metaphor"},{"time":382000,"text":"of a staircase in the mind."},{"time":384000,"text":"I'm saying we are Homo duplex"},{"time":386000,"text":"and this staircase takes us up from the profane level"},{"time":389000,"text":"to the level of the sacred."},{"time":391000,"text":"When we climb that staircase,"},{"time":393000,"text":"self-interest fades away,"},{"time":395000,"text":"we become just much less self-interested,"},{"time":397000,"text":"and we feel as though we are better, nobler"},{"time":399000,"text":"and somehow uplifted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402000,"text":"So here's the million-dollar question"},{"time":405000,"text":"for social scientists like me:"},{"time":407000,"text":"Is the staircase"},{"time":409000,"text":"a feature of our evolutionary design?"},{"time":412000,"text":"Is it a product of natural selection,"},{"time":415000,"text":"like our hands?"},{"time":417000,"text":"Or is it a bug, a mistake in the system --"},{"time":420000,"text":"this religious stuff is just something"},{"time":422000,"text":"that happens when the wires cross in the brain --"},{"time":425000,"text":"Jill has a stroke and she has this religious experience,"},{"time":427000,"text":"it's just a mistake?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"Well many scientists who study religion take this view."},{"time":433000,"text":"The New Atheists, for example,"},{"time":435000,"text":"argue that religion is a set of memes,"},{"time":437000,"text":"sort of parasitic memes,"},{"time":439000,"text":"that get inside our minds"},{"time":441000,"text":"and make us do all kinds of crazy religious stuff,"},{"time":444000,"text":"self-destructive stuff, like suicide bombing."},{"time":446000,"text":"And after all,"},{"time":448000,"text":"how could it ever be good for us"},{"time":450000,"text":"to lose ourselves?"},{"time":452000,"text":"How could it ever be adaptive"},{"time":454000,"text":"for any organism"},{"time":456000,"text":"to overcome self-interest?"},{"time":459000,"text":"Well let me show you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461000,"text":"In \"The Descent of Man,\""},{"time":463000,"text":"Charles Darwin wrote a great deal"},{"time":465000,"text":"about the evolution of morality --"},{"time":467000,"text":"where did it come from, why do we have it."},{"time":470000,"text":"Darwin noted that many of our virtues"},{"time":472000,"text":"are of very little use to ourselves,"},{"time":474000,"text":"but they're of great use to our groups."},{"time":476000,"text":"He wrote about the scenario"},{"time":478000,"text":"in which two tribes of early humans"},{"time":480000,"text":"would have come in contact and competition."},{"time":482000,"text":"He said, \"If the one tribe included"},{"time":485000,"text":"a great number of courageous, sympathetic"},{"time":487000,"text":"and faithful members"},{"time":489000,"text":"who are always ready to aid and defend each other,"},{"time":491000,"text":"this tribe would succeed better"},{"time":493000,"text":"and conquer the other.\""},{"time":495000,"text":"He went on to say that \"Selfish and contentious people"},{"time":497000,"text":"will not cohere,"},{"time":499000,"text":"and without coherence"},{"time":501000,"text":"nothing can be effected.\""},{"time":503000,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":505000,"text":"Charles Darwin believed"},{"time":507000,"text":"in group selection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509000,"text":"Now this idea has been very controversial for the last 40 years,"},{"time":512000,"text":"but it's about to make a major comeback this year,"},{"time":515000,"text":"especially after E.O. Wilson's book comes out in April,"},{"time":518000,"text":"making a very strong case"},{"time":520000,"text":"that we, and several other species,"},{"time":522000,"text":"are products of group selection."},{"time":524000,"text":"But really the way to think about this"},{"time":526000,"text":"is as multilevel selection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"So look at it this way:"},{"time":530000,"text":"You've got competition going on within groups and across groups."},{"time":533000,"text":"So here's a group of guys on a college crew team."},{"time":536000,"text":"Within this team"},{"time":538000,"text":"there's competition."},{"time":540000,"text":"There are guys competing with each other."},{"time":542000,"text":"The slowest rowers, the weakest rowers, are going to get cut from the team."},{"time":545000,"text":"And only a few of these guys are going to go on in the sport."},{"time":547000,"text":"Maybe one of them will make it to the Olympics."},{"time":550000,"text":"So within the team,"},{"time":552000,"text":"their interests are actually pitted against each other."},{"time":555000,"text":"And sometimes it would be advantageous"},{"time":557000,"text":"for one of these guys"},{"time":559000,"text":"to try to sabotage the other guys."},{"time":561000,"text":"Maybe he'll badmouth his chief rival"},{"time":563000,"text":"to the coach."},{"time":565000,"text":"But while that competition is going on"},{"time":567000,"text":"within the boat,"},{"time":569000,"text":"this competition is going on across boats."},{"time":572000,"text":"And once you put these guys in a boat competing with another boat,"},{"time":575000,"text":"now they've got no choice but to cooperate"},{"time":577000,"text":"because they're all in the same boat."},{"time":580000,"text":"They can only win"},{"time":582000,"text":"if they all pull together as a team."},{"time":584000,"text":"I mean, these things sound trite,"},{"time":586000,"text":"but they are deep evolutionary truths."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588000,"text":"The main argument against group selection"},{"time":590000,"text":"has always been"},{"time":592000,"text":"that, well sure, it would be nice to have a group of cooperators,"},{"time":595000,"text":"but as soon as you have a group of cooperators,"},{"time":597000,"text":"they're just going to get taken over by free-riders,"},{"time":600000,"text":"individuals that are going to exploit the hard work of the others."},{"time":603000,"text":"Let me illustrate this for you."},{"time":605000,"text":"Suppose we've got a group of little organisms --"},{"time":608000,"text":"they can be bacteria, they can be hamsters; it doesn't matter what --"},{"time":611000,"text":"and let's suppose that this little group here, they evolved to be cooperative."},{"time":614000,"text":"Well that's great. They graze, they defend each other,"},{"time":616000,"text":"they work together, they generate wealth."},{"time":619000,"text":"And as you'll see in this simulation,"},{"time":621000,"text":"as they interact they gain points, as it were, they grow,"},{"time":624000,"text":"and when they've doubled in size, you'll see them split,"},{"time":626000,"text":"and that's how they reproduce and the population grows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628000,"text":"But suppose then that one of them mutates."},{"time":631000,"text":"There's a mutation in the gene"},{"time":633000,"text":"and one of them mutates to follow a selfish strategy."},{"time":635000,"text":"It takes advantage of the others."},{"time":637000,"text":"And so when a green interacts with a blue,"},{"time":640000,"text":"you'll see the green gets larger and the blue gets smaller."},{"time":642000,"text":"So here's how things play out."},{"time":644000,"text":"We start with just one green,"},{"time":646000,"text":"and as it interacts"},{"time":648000,"text":"it gains wealth or points or food."},{"time":651000,"text":"And in short order, the cooperators are done for."},{"time":654000,"text":"The free-riders have taken over."},{"time":657000,"text":"If a group cannot solve the free-rider problem"},{"time":660000,"text":"then it cannot reap the benefits of cooperation"},{"time":663000,"text":"and group selection cannot get started."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666000,"text":"But there are solutions to the free-rider problem."},{"time":668000,"text":"It's not that hard a problem."},{"time":670000,"text":"In fact, nature has solved it many, many times."},{"time":673000,"text":"And nature's favorite solution"},{"time":675000,"text":"is to put everyone in the same boat."},{"time":678000,"text":"For example,"},{"time":680000,"text":"why is it that the mitochondria in every cell"},{"time":683000,"text":"has its own DNA,"},{"time":685000,"text":"totally separate from the DNA in the nucleus?"},{"time":688000,"text":"It's because they used to be"},{"time":690000,"text":"separate free-living bacteria"},{"time":692000,"text":"and they came together"},{"time":694000,"text":"and became a superorganism."},{"time":696000,"text":"Somehow or other -- maybe one swallowed another; we'll never know exactly why --"},{"time":699000,"text":"but once they got a membrane around them,"},{"time":701000,"text":"they were all in the same membrane,"},{"time":703000,"text":"now all the wealth-created division of labor,"},{"time":706000,"text":"all the greatness created by cooperation,"},{"time":708000,"text":"stays locked inside the membrane"},{"time":710000,"text":"and we've got a superorganism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713000,"text":"And now let's rerun the simulation"},{"time":715000,"text":"putting one of these superorganisms"},{"time":717000,"text":"into a population of free-riders, of defectors, of cheaters"},{"time":720000,"text":"and look what happens."},{"time":723000,"text":"A superorganism can basically take what it wants."},{"time":725000,"text":"It's so big and powerful and efficient"},{"time":728000,"text":"that it can take resources"},{"time":730000,"text":"from the greens, from the defectors, the cheaters."},{"time":734000,"text":"And pretty soon the whole population"},{"time":736000,"text":"is actually composed of these new superorganisms."},{"time":739000,"text":"What I've shown you here"},{"time":741000,"text":"is sometimes called a major transition"},{"time":743000,"text":"in evolutionary history."},{"time":746000,"text":"Darwin's laws don't change,"},{"time":748000,"text":"but now there's a new kind of player on the field"},{"time":751000,"text":"and things begin to look very different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754000,"text":"Now this transition was not a one-time freak of nature"},{"time":756000,"text":"that just happened with some bacteria."},{"time":758000,"text":"It happened again"},{"time":760000,"text":"about 120 or a 140 million years ago"},{"time":762000,"text":"when some solitary wasps"},{"time":765000,"text":"began creating little simple, primitive"},{"time":767000,"text":"nests, or hives."},{"time":770000,"text":"Once several wasps were all together in the same hive,"},{"time":773000,"text":"they had no choice but to cooperate,"},{"time":775000,"text":"because pretty soon they were locked into competition"},{"time":777000,"text":"with other hives."},{"time":779000,"text":"And the most cohesive hives won,"},{"time":781000,"text":"just as Darwin said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"These early wasps"},{"time":785000,"text":"gave rise to the bees and the ants"},{"time":787000,"text":"that have covered the world"},{"time":789000,"text":"and changed the biosphere."},{"time":791000,"text":"And it happened again,"},{"time":793000,"text":"even more spectacularly,"},{"time":795000,"text":"in the last half-million years"},{"time":797000,"text":"when our own ancestors"},{"time":799000,"text":"became cultural creatures,"},{"time":801000,"text":"they came together around a hearth or a campfire,"},{"time":804000,"text":"they divided labor,"},{"time":806000,"text":"they began painting their bodies, they spoke their own dialects,"},{"time":809000,"text":"and eventually they worshiped their own gods."},{"time":812000,"text":"Once they were all in the same tribe,"},{"time":814000,"text":"they could keep the benefits of cooperation locked inside."},{"time":817000,"text":"And they unlocked the most powerful force"},{"time":819000,"text":"ever known on this planet,"},{"time":821000,"text":"which is human cooperation --"},{"time":823000,"text":"a force for construction"},{"time":825000,"text":"and destruction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828000,"text":"Of course, human groups are nowhere near as cohesive"},{"time":830000,"text":"as beehives."},{"time":832000,"text":"Human groups may look like hives for brief moments,"},{"time":835000,"text":"but they tend to then break apart."},{"time":837000,"text":"We're not locked into cooperation the way bees and ants are."},{"time":840000,"text":"In fact, often,"},{"time":842000,"text":"as we've seen happen in a lot of the Arab Spring revolts,"},{"time":844000,"text":"often those divisions are along religious lines."},{"time":848000,"text":"Nonetheless, when people do come together"},{"time":851000,"text":"and put themselves all into the same movement,"},{"time":853000,"text":"they can move mountains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856000,"text":"Look at the people in these photos I've been showing you."},{"time":859000,"text":"Do you think they're there"},{"time":861000,"text":"pursuing their self-interest?"},{"time":863000,"text":"Or are they pursuing communal interest,"},{"time":866000,"text":"which requires them to lose themselves"},{"time":869000,"text":"and become simply a part of a whole?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":874000,"text":"Okay, so that was my Talk"},{"time":876000,"text":"delivered in the standard TED way."},{"time":878000,"text":"And now I'm going to give the whole Talk over again"},{"time":880000,"text":"in three minutes"},{"time":882000,"text":"in a more full-spectrum sort of way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":885000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":887000,"text":"(Video) Jonathan Haidt: We humans have many varieties"},{"time":889000,"text":"of religious experience,"},{"time":891000,"text":"as William James explained."},{"time":893000,"text":"One of the most common is climbing the secret staircase"},{"time":896000,"text":"and losing ourselves."},{"time":898000,"text":"The staircase takes us"},{"time":900000,"text":"from the experience of life as profane or ordinary"},{"time":903000,"text":"upwards to the experience of life as sacred,"},{"time":905000,"text":"or deeply interconnected."},{"time":907000,"text":"We are Homo duplex,"},{"time":909000,"text":"as Durkheim explained."},{"time":911000,"text":"And we are Homo duplex"},{"time":913000,"text":"because we evolved by multilevel selection,"},{"time":915000,"text":"as Darwin explained."},{"time":918000,"text":"I can't be certain if the staircase is an adaptation"},{"time":920000,"text":"rather than a bug,"},{"time":922000,"text":"but if it is an adaptation,"},{"time":924000,"text":"then the implications are profound."},{"time":926000,"text":"If it is an adaptation,"},{"time":928000,"text":"then we evolved to be religious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931000,"text":"I don't mean that we evolved"},{"time":933000,"text":"to join gigantic organized religions."},{"time":935000,"text":"Those things came along too recently."},{"time":937000,"text":"I mean that we evolved"},{"time":939000,"text":"to see sacredness all around us"},{"time":941000,"text":"and to join with others into teams"},{"time":943000,"text":"and circle around sacred objects,"},{"time":945000,"text":"people and ideas."},{"time":947000,"text":"This is why politics is so tribal."},{"time":950000,"text":"Politics is partly profane, it's partly about self-interest,"},{"time":953000,"text":"but politics is also about sacredness."},{"time":956000,"text":"It's about joining with others"},{"time":958000,"text":"to pursue moral ideas."},{"time":960000,"text":"It's about the eternal struggle between good and evil,"},{"time":963000,"text":"and we all believe we're on the good team."}]},{"cues":[{"time":966000,"text":"And most importantly,"},{"time":968000,"text":"if the staircase is real,"},{"time":970000,"text":"it explains the persistent undercurrent"},{"time":972000,"text":"of dissatisfaction in modern life."},{"time":974000,"text":"Because human beings are, to some extent,"},{"time":977000,"text":"hivish creatures like bees."},{"time":979000,"text":"We're bees. We busted out of the hive during the Enlightenment."},{"time":982000,"text":"We broke down the old institutions"},{"time":985000,"text":"and brought liberty to the oppressed."},{"time":987000,"text":"We unleashed Earth-changing creativity"},{"time":989000,"text":"and generated vast wealth and comfort."}]},{"cues":[{"time":992000,"text":"Nowadays we fly around"},{"time":994000,"text":"like individual bees exulting in our freedom."},{"time":996000,"text":"But sometimes we wonder:"},{"time":998000,"text":"Is this all there is?"},{"time":1000000,"text":"What should I do with my life?"},{"time":1002000,"text":"What's missing?"},{"time":1004000,"text":"What's missing is that we are Homo duplex,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"but modern, secular society was built"},{"time":1009000,"text":"to satisfy our lower, profane selves."},{"time":1012000,"text":"It's really comfortable down here on the lower level."},{"time":1015000,"text":"Come, have a seat in my home entertainment center."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1018000,"text":"One great challenge of modern life"},{"time":1020000,"text":"is to find the staircase amid all the clutter"},{"time":1023000,"text":"and then to do something good and noble"},{"time":1026000,"text":"once you climb to the top."},{"time":1029000,"text":"I see this desire in my students at the University of Virginia."},{"time":1032000,"text":"They all want to find a cause or calling"},{"time":1034000,"text":"that they can throw themselves into."},{"time":1036000,"text":"They're all searching for their staircase."},{"time":1039000,"text":"And that gives me hope"},{"time":1041000,"text":"because people are not purely selfish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1043000,"text":"Most people long to overcome pettiness"},{"time":1045000,"text":"and become part of something larger."},{"time":1047000,"text":"And this explains the extraordinary resonance"},{"time":1050000,"text":"of this simple metaphor"},{"time":1052000,"text":"conjured up nearly 400 years ago."},{"time":1055000,"text":"\"No man is an island"},{"time":1057000,"text":"entire of itself."},{"time":1059000,"text":"Every man is a piece of the continent,"},{"time":1062000,"text":"a part of the main.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1065000,"text":"JH: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1067000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}